<h3>What to do when a check fails</h3>
<p>A failed check means the article goes back, not out. Common failures and fixes:</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Plagiarism above 5%.</strong> Rewrite the flagged paragraphs in your own words. Do not paraphrase, recompose.</li>
<li><strong>Stat without a source.</strong> Find a source or delete the stat. Never publish unsourced numbers.</li>
<li><strong>Voice drift.</strong> Run the humanize pass again on the offending section.</li>
<li><strong>Missing internal link.</strong> Add it. Use our <a href="/blog/internal-linking-blog-posts/">internal linking guide for blog posts</a> to find a good target.</li>
</ul>
<p>A hybrid program lives or dies by its quality gate. The teams that ship anyway are the teams that lose rankings.</p>
